{
  "page": "Rhaenys Targaryen (disambiguation)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a></b> was a sister-wife and queen of King Aegon I Targaryen.\n</p><p><br />\n<b>Rhaenys Targaryen</b> is also the name of several other members of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>. These include:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>, also known as the <i>Queen Who Never Was</i>, only daughter of Prince Aemon Targaryen and Lady Jocelyn Baratheon.</li>\n<li>Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Rhaegar)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Rhaegar)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>, only daughter of Prince Rhaegar Targaryen and Princess Elia Martell.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rhaenys_Targaryen_(disambiguation)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys\" title=\"Rhaenys\">Rhaenys</a> (disambiguation)</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403151654\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.005 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.005 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 3/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</